```text
                ┌───────────────────┐
                │ Prometheus        │
                │ Alibaba Trace     │
                │ Google Trace      │
                └─────────┬─────────┘
                          │
                          ▼
                 Data Ingestion Layer
                          │
                          ▼
                 Data Cleaning Layer
                          │
                          ▼
                Anomaly Detection
                          │
                          ▼
                Feature Engineering
                          │
                          ▼
                  Parquet Storage
                          │
                          ▼
                 AI/ML Training Data
```

---

# 3. Project Structure

Explain each folder.

## configs/

Contains configuration files.

```text
configs/
└── metrics.yaml
```

Purpose:

* Metrics to collect
* Polling intervals
* Thresholds
* Feature settings

Think of it as:

> The control center of the pipeline.

---

## ingestion/

Responsible for acquiring telemetry.

### prometheus_collector.py

Connects to Prometheus.

Collects:

```text
CPU Usage
Memory Usage
Replica Count
Network Metrics
```

Output:

```text
timestamp
cluster_id
pod
namespace
cpu
memory
replicas
```

---

### fetch_alibaba.py

Loads Alibaba Cluster Trace datasets.

Used for:

```text
Historical workload analysis
Training forecasting models
```

---

### fetch_google.py

Loads Google Cluster Trace datasets.

Used for:

```text
Large-scale workload patterns
Real-world scaling behavior
```

---

# 4. Preprocessing Layer

This is where raw telemetry becomes usable.

---

## cleaner.py

### Duplicate Removal

Sometimes collectors produce duplicate entries.

Example:

```text
10:00 CPU=45
10:00 CPU=45
```

Cleaner keeps only the latest.

---

### Missing Value Handling

Infrastructure metrics often contain gaps.

Example:

```text
45
46
NULL
48
```

The cleaner fills the missing value.

Methods:

```text
Forward Fill
Backward Fill
Linear Interpolation
```

---

### Time Alignment

Raw metrics arrive at irregular intervals.

Example:

```text
10:00:03
10:00:27
10:01:14
```

AI models prefer consistent intervals.

Cleaner converts them into:

```text
10:00
10:01
10:02
```

using 1-minute windows.

---

## anomaly_detector.py

Detects abnormal behavior.

Examples:

```text
CPU suddenly jumps
50 → 98%
```

or

```text
Memory spikes unexpectedly
```

Methods:

### Z-Score

Measures how far a value is from normal behavior.

### IQR

Detects extreme outliers.

Purpose:

```text
Remove noise
Improve model accuracy
```

---

# 5. Feature Engineering Layer

Most important AI component.

Raw CPU values alone are not enough.

We create advanced features.

---

## Resource Features

```text
cpu_avg
cpu_max
cpu_min

memory_avg
memory_max
memory_min
```

These summarize infrastructure behavior.

---

## Scaling Features

```text
replica_count
change_rate
trend_strength
```

Used to understand scaling patterns.

---

## Rolling Statistics

Created by feature_builder.py

Example:

```text
rolling_mean_5m
rolling_mean_15m
rolling_std
```

Purpose:

Detect workload trends.

---

## Cost Features

Generated automatically.

```text
estimated_compute_cost
estimated_gpu_cost
```

Purpose:

Optimize not only performance but also cost.

---

## Sustainability Features

```text
power_usage_kwh
co2_estimate
```

Purpose:

Support Green AI and sustainable infrastructure.

---

## Forecast Labels

The pipeline also generates future targets.

Example:

```text
future_cpu_5m
future_cpu_15m
future_cpu_30m
```

These are critical.

The AI model learns:

```text
Current State
      ↓
Predict Future CPU Demand
      ↓
Scaling Decision
```

---

# 6. Storage Layer

## parquet_writer.py

Stores processed data as Parquet files.

Example:

```text
data/
└── processed/
    └── test_dataset/
        └── 2026/
            └── 06/
                └── 06/
                    └── data_214015.parquet
```

Why Parquet?

```text
Smaller storage
Faster queries
ML-friendly
Cloud-native
```

---

# 7. Pipeline Orchestration

## main.py

Acts as the workflow controller.

Flow:

```text
Collect Metrics
      ↓
Clean Data
      ↓
Detect Anomalies
      ↓
Build Features
      ↓
Store Dataset
```

